<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1825,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="526">
This species is widespread in the Neotropical Region, from 
<collectingCountry box="[857,916,1825,1850]" name="Cuba" pageId="6" pageNumber="526">Cuba</collectingCountry>
in the Greater Antilles to 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1344,1825,1850]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="526">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Pérez- 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,454,1861,1886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="526" refId="ref6294" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. &amp; Floriano, C. F. B. (2016) New records of the water strider Platyvelia brachialis (Stal 1860) (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) from the Dominican Republic and Haiti, with a checklist of the West Indian Veliidae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 118, 471 - 476. https: // doi. org / 10.4289 / 0013 - 8797.118.3.471" type="journal article">Gelabert &amp; Floriano 2016</bibRefCitation>
), living preferentially in small temporary rain pools. We present here the first record from 
<collectingRegion box="[212,382,1897,1922]" country="France" name="Guyane" pageId="6" pageNumber="526">
<collectingCountry box="[212,382,1897,1922]" name="French Guiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="526">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
